The paper is about Automated Machine Learning (AutoML), which is a subfield of Machine Learning (ML). The use of a graph-based architecture and evolutionary algorithm suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of Bayesian hyper-parameter optimization suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence). The paper's focus on ML models and their combinations suggests that it may also fall under the categories of "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and "cs.CV" (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of datasets suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms).
